comment.narrative: According to data collected by the Department of Statistics on enrolment in operating classrooms financed by the Project.

title.narrative: 500 NGOs# run KG classrooms refurbished in targeted areas with support from the World Bank loan

comment.narrative: According to data provided by the MOE ECEEP team.

title.narrative: 750 public KG classrooms built in targeted areas with support from the World Bank loan

comment.narrative: According to data provided by the MOE ECEEP team.

title.narrative: 2,000 KG classrooms in targeted areas receive learning materials

comment.narrative: Another 1,106 packages are scheduled for delivery prior to Project closing. This means that the Project will fall short of thetargeted 2,000 packages.

title.narrative: (a) 2,700 communities reached by 2010 in disadvantaged project areas and (b) all KGs supported with adequate O&M and educational materials in disadvantaged project areas

comment.narrative: The 2010 restructuring changed some of the original PAD indicators but made no mention of this indicator. However, this indicatorwas no longer tracked. At the time of the final ISR, the advice of MNADE was to reintroduce this indicator into the ISR since itwas never dropped.
